  "claim_short": "This packet proves a negative answer for the natural class of finite tree metrics whose tree vertices are exactly the metric points. If T is a finite weighted tree and rho is its path metric on V(T), then (V(T),rho) is not WLR whenever |V(T)| >= 5. For four tree vertices, the only WLR case is the weighted tripod K_{1,3}, which is exactly the four-point family already listed in the source paper.",
